A fisherman has been taken by a crocodile while he was trying to retrieve his fishing equipment at  Northern Territory's Adelaide River.

Police told Daily Mail Australia that the 57-year-old was standing on the bank of the river, east of Darwin, at about 5.30pm on Monday.

The man was reportedly fishing with his wife when he was killed by the crocodile and she witnessed the attack.

