Police reported the fisherman was trying to retrieve a fishing hook, which had become snagged.

'It appears he has entered the water and tragically was taken by a crocodile while retrieving fishing equipment,' a police spokesman said.

Police, NT Emergency Services and the Parks & Wildlife Crocodile Management Team shot and killed a crocodile at about 9.30pm and recovered a body, believed to be that of the victim.

A coronial inquest is currently being conducted.

The man's wife was treated for shock and returned to her home in rural Darwin after the incident, reported the NT News.

